    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a Lecturer (≈ Assistant Professor) in Natural Language Processing at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edinburghnlp.inf.ed.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Edinburgh&lt;/a&gt;, where I am part of the Institute for Language, Cognition, and Computation (&lt;a href=&#34;https://web.inf.ed.ac.uk/ilcc&#34;&gt;ILCC&lt;/a&gt;), and an Affiliated Lecturer at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://ltl.mmll.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a prospective student, collaborator, or industry partner please visit the &lt;a href=&#34;faq&#34;&gt;FAQ&lt;/a&gt; page for more information.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previously, I was a visiting postdoctoral scholar at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.stanford.edu/&#34;&gt;Stanford University&lt;/a&gt; and a postdoctoral fellow in computer science at &lt;a href=&#34;https://mila.quebec/en/&#34;&gt;Mila - Quebec AI Institute&lt;/a&gt; in Montreal. In 2021, I obtained a PhD in computational linguistics from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/&#34;&gt;St John&amp;rsquo;s College&lt;/a&gt;. I interned as AI/ML researcher at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.apple.com/&#34;&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt; in Cupertino.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main research foci of my lab are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;modular deep learning&lt;/strong&gt; [&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.11529&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;]: designing neural architectures that route information to specialised, autonomous modules. This includes sparse adaptation for parameter-efficient fine-tuning [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2022.acl-long.125/&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;], recombing skills for systematic generalisation [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2021.tacl-1.25/&#34;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2023.eacl-main.49.pdf&#34;&gt;4&lt;/a&gt;], and model merging [&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.17574&#34;&gt;5&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;grounding&lt;/strong&gt;: language learning and use in perception and action, taking into account the world&amp;rsquo;s cross-cultural diversity [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2021.emnlp-main.818/&#34;&gt;6&lt;/a&gt;], integrating vision into language models [&lt;a href=&#34;https://proceedings.mlr.press/v162/bugliarello22a.html&#34;&gt;7&lt;/a&gt;], and probing LLMs for the temporal aspects of their internal world model;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;computational typology&lt;/strong&gt; [&lt;a href=&#34;https://direct.mit.edu/coli/article/45/3/559/93372/Modeling-Language-Variation-and-Universals-A&#34;&gt;8&lt;/a&gt;]: using computational tools to study the cross-lingual variation of the world&amp;rsquo;s languages scientifically [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2023.sigtyp-1.18.pdf&#34;&gt;9&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/2102.05717&#34;&gt;10&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;multilingual natural language processing&lt;/strong&gt;: developing language technology in a diverse range of languages, by finding the correct inductive biases for sample efficient learning [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/D19-1288/&#34;&gt;11&lt;/a&gt;] or jointly learning how to translate and classify / generate [&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/2107.11353&#34;&gt;12&lt;/a&gt;]; creating new annotated multilingual datasets [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2020.emnlp-main.185/&#34;&gt;13&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://direct.mit.edu/coli/article/46/4/847/97326/Multi-SimLex-A-Large-Scale-Evaluation-of&#34;&gt;14&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;tokenization-free language modelling&lt;/strong&gt;: jointly performing input segmentation and self-supervised learning, by inducing hierarchical abstractions on top of raw inputs [&lt;a href=&#34;https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.353/&#34;&gt;15&lt;/a&gt;].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My research earned a &lt;a href=&#34;https://ai.google/research/outreach/faculty-research-awards/&#34;&gt;Google Research Faculty Award&lt;/a&gt;. I received 2 Best Paper Awards at &lt;a href=&#34;https://2021.emnlp.org/blog/2021-10-29-best-paper-awards/&#34;&gt;EMNLP 2021&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/W19-4310.pdf&#34;&gt;RepL4NLP 2019&lt;/a&gt;. I am a board member of &lt;a href=&#34;https://sigtyp.github.io/&#34;&gt;SIGTYP&lt;/a&gt;, the ACL special interest group for computational typology, a scholar of the European Lab for Learning and Intelligent Systems (&lt;a href=&#34;https://ellis.eu/fellows&#34;&gt;ELLIS&lt;/a&gt;), and part of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://transacl.org/index.php/tacl&#34;&gt;TACL&lt;/a&gt; journal editorial team. I am a scientific advisor for the AI company &lt;a href=&#34;https://ivadolabs.com/en/&#34;&gt;Ivado Labs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
